On Sun, 29 Sep 2002, Tom Megow wrote:

> Another son of mine has a 66 split window bus.I am needing to replace the
> passengers side
> taillight because the battery has been slamming into it. There was no
> battery tie down when we bought it. Our current battery is probably larger
> that the old 6V (if my memory serves me right)
> Before I buy a generic and start drilling holes is there any better choices
> out there. There seems to be some metal projection on the battery area
> floor(?) and one on the wall behind(?) the battery. There is no rust in the
> area now, I am afriad drilling holes will make the battery area vulnerable
> to it.

If you have room, nothing beats a marine-style battery box.  You may have
to drill some holes in the floor for the tie-down strap anchors, but with
proper sealing they won't be a source of corrosion, particularly if the
battery acid is now contained in the box.

George
